title: cuisine-carbonara
caption: Carbonara
tags: cuisine
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Spaghetti or rigatoni with guanciale (cured pork cheek), eggs, Pecorino Romano, and black pepper — no cream, ever.  The sauce forms from the residual heat of the pasta emulsifying the egg and cheese with a little pasta water.  Rome's most argued-over dish.
